                            <comment id="12407043" author="brentworden" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2004 22:41:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=12181)&lt;br/&gt;
clearXMLProperties patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407044" author="brentworden" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2004 22:51:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For the configuration:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item name=&quot;one&quot;&amp;gt;one&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;two&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item name=&quot;three&quot;&amp;gt;three&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;four&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;five&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;six&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch results in the following behavior changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for conf.clearProperty(&quot;list&quot;) the resulting configuration is:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for conf.clearProperty(&quot;list.item&quot;) the resulting configuration is:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;five&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;six&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for conf.clearProperty(&quot;list.item&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;@name&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;) the resulting configuration is:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;one&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;two&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;three&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;four&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;five&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;item&amp;gt;six&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/sublist&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407045" author="ebourg" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2004 22:54:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you Brent, I&apos;m already working on a patch with a recursive implementation&lt;br/&gt;
of clearXmlProperty but your test case is interesting. Given the following&lt;br/&gt;
configuration:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;configuration&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;item name=&quot;foo&quot;&amp;gt;bar&amp;lt;/item&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/list&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;calling clearProperty(&quot;list&quot;) should not remove the &quot;list.item&quot; property, and&lt;br/&gt;
calling clearProperty(&quot;list.item&quot;) should not remove the &quot;list.item&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;@name&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
property.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407046" author="brentworden" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2004 23:26:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I can make a couple changes to the patch to achieve the desired &lt;br/&gt;
results.  Stay tuned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, automated testing is somewhat difficult without visibility to the actual &lt;br/&gt;
XML properties.  Would it make sence to add at least a getter for XML propeties &lt;br/&gt;
which query the actual DOM structure and not the map in BaseConfiguation?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407047" author="brentworden" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2004 23:37:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=12183)&lt;br/&gt;
New patch with changes suggested by Emmanuel.  Disregard previous patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407048" author="dep4b" created="Thu, 12 Aug 2004 23:50:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brent..  I added the unit test stuff in, but not the patch.  I think another&lt;br/&gt;
patch maybe fixed the issue..  Can you verify it works for you?  If not, please&lt;br/&gt;
reopen this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407049" author="dep4b" created="Thu, 12 Aug 2004 23:56:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, and the xml getter sounds like a good idea.  I have no problems adding&lt;br/&gt;
helper methods etc on specific implementations of Configuration...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;toXml would be nice!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407050" author="brentworden" created="Sat, 14 Aug 2004 05:23:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The clearXmlProperty still isn&apos;t handling list properties correctly.  I &lt;br/&gt;
reimplemented it and added a getXmlProperty method to help with testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the new changes, if one clears a property, subsequent calls to &lt;br/&gt;
getXmlProperty return null.  This isn&apos;t the case with the current &lt;br/&gt;
clearXmlProperty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407051" author="brentworden" created="Sat, 14 Aug 2004 05:24:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created an attachment (id=12427)&lt;br/&gt;
patch with getXmlProperty and new clearXmlProperty to handle list properties correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407052" author="ebourg" created="Mon, 6 Sep 2004 19:23:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s left on this bug ? It seems the patch was applied, is it ok now ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407053" author="dep4b" created="Fri, 10 Sep 2004 20:46:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this bug is fixed.  Brent, if not, please let us know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12407054" author="brentworden" created="Sat, 11 Sep 2004 09:23:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Everything looks to be in place and working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
